Show HN: Hacker News Who's Hiring Semantic Search
text:
Wrote a proof of concept script for searching for jobs by copy pasting your resume. It looks for jobs posted on Hacker News Who’s Hiring from the past 3 months: https://colab.research.google.com/drive/12wt7cjhIUKf1Vu2rRFO...

To use it, click Runtime > Run All. Wait about 5 minutes, then once everything is done, go to the bottom most cell and you can change the query variable from my resume to yours, and then re-run the cell.

Largely written by GPT-4 and copy pasting documentation, with some minor tweaking.

Tell HN: Robocallers are now pretending to be live humans
text:
I've gotten several marketing calls where the voice on the end sounded human. But if you ignore the question they ask and say something simple but unexpected, they aren't able to respond. ("What day is it?" "Prove to me that you're a live human. What's the first letter of that name you just gave me...")

I think one tactic is to bring in a live person, but then have them record (from a script) -- and then swap in those recorded responses at appropriate times. (That happened to me this morning -- but they kept playing the same recording.) What was especially frustrating about that was that they'd had them record the phrase "I AM a live person -- but I'm reading from a script." (And then they played that identical recording, twice in a row...)

Now that this is happening, I'm not sure what my response should be. (Don't answer the phone; take the call and waste their time; spread mass awareness and push for government regulations...?)
